<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>IAEA Programme and Appropriation Structure</TITLE>
<META name="docid" content="prindex">
<META name="author" content="webmaster@www.iaea.or.at">
<META name="expires" content="25 June 1996">
<META name="url"  content="http://www.iaea.or.at/programmes/index.htm">
<META name="type" content="edit">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1>IAEA Programme and Appropriation Structure</H1>
<H2>MAJOR PROGRAMME 1: NUCLEAR POWER AND FUEL CYCLE </H2>
<UL>
<H3><LI>A Nuclear Power</H3>
  <UL>
  <LI>A.1 Nuclear Power Planning
  <LI>A.2 Nuclear Power Implementation and Performance
  <LI>A.3 Advanced Reactors and Applications
  <LI>A.4 Nuclear Fusion
  </UL>
<H3><LI>B Nuclear Fuel Cycle and Waste Technology</H3>
  <UL>
  <LI>B.1 Raw Materials for Reactor Fuels
  <LI>B.2 Reactor Fuel Technology and Performance
  <LI>B.3 Spent Fuel Management
  <LI>B.4 Information on Nuclear Fuel Cycle
  <LI>B.5 Handling, Treatment, Conditioning, and Storage of Radioactive Wastes 
  <LI>B.6 Radioactive Waste Disposal
  <LI>B.7 Decontamination and Decommissioning of Nuclear Installations
  <LI>B.8 Waste Technology Planning and Support
  </UL>
<H3><LI>C Comparative Assessment of Energy Sources</H3>
  <UL>
  <LI>C.1 Energy Demand Analysis and Supply Options
  <LI>C.2 Health and Environmental Impacts and Risks of Energy Systems
  <LI>C.3 Sustainable Energy Options
  <LI>C.4 Support for Comparative Assessments
  </UL>
</UL>
<hr>
<H2>MAJOR PROGRAMME 2: NUCLEAR APPLICATIONS</H2>
<UL>
<H3><LI>D Food and Agriculture</H3>
  <UL>
  <LI>D.1 Soil Fertility, Irrigation and Crop Production
  <LI>D.2 Plant Breeding and Genetics
  <LI>D.3 Animal Production and Health
  <LI>D.4 Insect and Pest Control
  <LI>D.5 Agrochemicals and Residues
  <LI>D.6 Food Preservation
  </UL>
<H3><LI>E Human Health</H3>
  <UL>
  <LI>E.1 Nuclear Medicine 
  <LI>E.2 Applied Radiation Biology and Radiotherapy
  <LI>E.3 Dosimetry
  <LI>E.4 Nutritional and Health-related Environmental Studies
  </UL>
<H3><LI>F Marine Environment, Water Resources and Industry </H3>
  <UL>
  <LI>F.1 Measurement and Assessment of Radionuclides in the Marine Environment
  <LI>F.2 Transfer of Radionuclides in the Marine Environment
  <LI>F.3 Monitoring and Study of Marine Pollution
  <LI>F.4 Development and Management of Water Resources
  <LI>F.5 Industrial Applications
  </UL>
<H3><LI>G Physical and Chemical Sciences</H3>
  <UL>
  <LI>G.1 Nuclear and Atomic Data for Applications
  <LI>G.2 Nuclear Instrumentation
  <LI>G.3 Theoretical Physics
  <LI>G.4 Utilization of Research Reactors and Particle Accelerators
  <LI>G.5 Radiochemical Applications
  <LI>G.6 Plasma Applications and Controlled Nuclear Fusion 
  </UL>
</UL>
