<HR>

<table width=90%>
   <tr>
   <th rowspan=2 nowrap> <IMG ALIGN=top SRC="/images/iaeasmall.gif">
   </tr>
   <tr>
   <td align=right>
   <h3>International Atomic Energy Agency<BR>Department of Safeguards</H3>
   
   </tr>
</table>

<HR size=5>
<center><H2>Welcome to IAEA Safeguards! </H2>
 <IMG align=top  SRC="homepg.jpg">
 </center>

<Blockquote>The Department of Safeguards is one of the five departments of
the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). The department has been
established in response to Article III, paragraph A.5 of the <A HREF="http://www.iaea.or.at/worldatom/glance/profile/statute.html"
>Agency's Statute</A>, which authorizes the IAEA

<BLOCKQUOTE>  "to establish and
administer safeguards designed to ensure that special fissionable and
other material, services, equipment, facilities and information... are
not used in such a way as to further any military purpose."
</BLOCKQUOTE> </Blockquote>

<HR>
<H4><U>Publications:</U></H4>
<UL>
   <LI><A HREF="pia38.htm">Against the Spread of Nuclear Weapons: IAEA Safeguards in the 1990s </A>
   <LI><A HREF="essir94.htm">Safeguards Implementation, 1994</A>
   <LI><A HREF="/worldatom/inforesource/bulletin/bull371/pellaud.html">IAEA safeguards in the 1990s: Building from experience</A>
</UL>
<H4><A HREF="/worldatom/inforesource/annual/anr9412.html">IAEA 1994 
Annual Report, excerpt for Safeguards</A></H4>

 <H4>For further information on 
Safeguards see <a href="/worldatom/program/safeguards/">Nuclear 
Safeguards and Verification under WorldAtom</A></H4>
<HR>                                                            

<p>
<IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="smbook.gif">
Thank you for visiting the IAEA Safeguards home page.
</P> 
