<TITLE>
Isotopes in Water and Environmental Management
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC=/worldatom/inforesource/other/gallery/is8.gif WIDTH=300
HEIGHT=200>
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>
<HR width=60%>
<CENTER>
<I>
This booklet presents a brief profile of recent achievements in
isotope hydrology and the involvement of the IAEA in this field. 
The principal responsibilities of the IAEA are transferring
technologies, coordinating scientific research, managing
specialized projects and maintaining analytical quality control. 
Agency scientists and facilities also serve as both focal points
and promoters for worldwide activities in isotope hydrology.</I>
<P>
For further information and publications please contact:
<P>
<B>
Mr. Klaus Froehlich, Section Head
<BR>
Isotope Hydrology
<BR>
Division of Physical and Chemical Sciences
<BR>
Department of Research and Isotopes
<BR>
IAEA, P.O. Box 100
<BR>
A-1400 Vienna, Austria
<BR>
Tel: 43-1-2060 2 1735
Fax: 43-1-2060 7
</B>
</CENTER>
