<TITLE>
1996 IAEA Yearbook
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<H2>IAEA Yearbook 1996</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<B>NUCLEAR SAFETY REVIEW 1996
<BR>
Part D of the IAEA Yearbook 1996</B>
<P>
The report features a number of prominent issues, focusing on their implications for radiation, waste and nuclear safety. There are discussions on a global nuclear safety culture, reactor pressure vessel annealing, regulatory aspects of safety related software, effects of low dose radiation, implementing radiation safety standards and the consequences of the Chernobyl accident. Articles focusing on radioactive waste safety deal with such issues as controls on the discharge of radioactive material and the handling of radioactive issues from past activities. 
<P>
<I>Contents:</I>  A global nuclear safety culture;  Nuclear safety - topical issues;  Radiation safety - topical issues;  Radioactive waste safety - topical issues.
<P>
STI/PUB/1019 (64 pp., 18 figures;  1996)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-103496-2
<BR>
Price: 140 Austrian Schillings
<P>
