<META name="type" content="edit">
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR=#545454>
<B><I>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2>Section Head</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.: 97/004</FONT>
<BR><STRONG>Grade:</STRONG> P-5
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>Organizational Unit</STRONG>
<BR>
Programme & Budget Section,Division of Budget & Finance
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B> 15 January 1997
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B> 15 April 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B> as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B> Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B> Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.A.01.c
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B></center>
<P>
Under the guidance of the Division Director, to manage the Section
which has responsibility for providing budgetary support services to
the Department Heads, Programme Managers and Member States, to
participate in the development of policy and in decision-making
processes, to assist the Director in advising the policy making
organs and Member States' representatives, the Agency's executive
management and programme managers on all aspects of the budgeting
system during all phases of planning and implementation.

<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
- To assist the Director in advising the policy making organs and
Member States' representatives, executive management and programme
managers on programme and budgetary matters, to make proposals and
offer solutions for problems;
<BR>
- To manage the preparation of the budget and the formulation of the
budget documents for the 6 major programmes, 20 programmes and 73
subprogrammes at the different stages of the budget cycle;
<BR>
- To analyse programme and budget proposals made by programme managers
and evaluate funds from all sources required for the achievement of
the planned output;
<BR>
- To direct and co-ordinate cost analyses, manpower and salary
forecasts, inflationary trends, standard cost calculations, analyses
of the impact of currency fluctuations and similar studies required
as a backup for the programme and budgeting process.
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	Advanced university degree in economics, business
administration, management or equivalent.  Knowledge of United
Nations practices and procedures desirable.  Excellent drafting and
presentation skills in English essential.  15 years' experience in
the analysis of fiscal operations and in the preparation and
management of large and complex budgets.  Ability to plan, integrate
and co-ordinate the work of assigned staff and to apply the
principles of human resources management in guiding staff to achieve stated objectives.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
