<FONT SIZE=+2>	Policy Officer <BR> Vacancy Notice No.: 96/080</FONT><BR><strong>Grade:</strong>	P-4
<HR NOSHADE><strong>Organizational Unit</strong><br>	Safeguards & Non-Proliferation Policy Section
	Division of External Relations
<BR></CENTER><P><UL><LI><B>Date:</B> 10 October 1996<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	10 January 1997    
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.A.10.b
</UL><P><HR width=40% NOSHADE><CENTER><B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B><HR width=40% NOSHADE><B><I>In general</I></B></center><P>
Under the general supervision of the Head of the Safeguards & Non-Proliferation Policy Section, to participate in the development and co-ordination of safeguards policy and to work on wider nuclear non-proliferation issues.

<P><CENTER><B><I>In particular</I></B></CENTER><P>- To assist in the preparation and co-ordination of the policy aspects of safeguards agreements and subsidiary arrangements including co-ordinating and/or participating in the process of their negotiation;<BR>
- To assist in the preparation of submissions about safeguards agreements as well as policy issues arising therefrom, to the Agency's Policy Making Organs;<BR>
- To assist in the preparation of safeguards policy studies and safeguards related documentation for internal use and, as appropriate, external presentation or publication;<BR>
- To monitor, analyse and where appropriate follow up developments in the areas of nuclear non-proliferation and disarmament;<BR>
- To assist as required with other areas of the Division's responsibilities.<BR>




<P><HR width=25% NOSHADE><center><B>QUALIFICATIONS</B><HR width=25% NOSHADE></center><P><B>Essential:</B>	Advanced university degree preferably in political science or international law.  Ten years experience including at least five years experience at international level.  Good analytical ability and excellent drafting skills.

<BR><B>Desirable:</B>	Knowledge of and experience in safeguards, nuclear non-proliferation and related disarmament and arms control issues.

<BR><B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish essential.  Knowledge of French, Spanish or Russian highly desirable.
<P>

<HR NOSHADE><P>Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars 
                          and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=10 CELLSPACING=10 CELLPADDING=10><TR><TD><STRONG>Rate</TD><TD>Net Base Salary</TD><TD>Post Adjustment</STRONG></TD></TR><TR><TD><STRONG>Single</STRONG></TD><TD>$45,413.-		</TD><TD>$31,971.-
</TD></TR><TR><TD><STRONG>Dependency</STRONG></TD><TD>$48,824.-</TD><TD>$34,372.-</TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER><P>Post Adjustment is variable and subject to change without notice.
