<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.: 97/003</TITLE>
<META name="docid" content="97/003">
<META name="author" content="adpi">
<META name="expires" content="1997-05-15>
<META name="type" content="edit">
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR=#545454>
<B><I>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Section Head</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.: 97/003</FONT>
<BR>
<STRONG>Grade:</STRONG>	P-5
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>Organizational Unit</STRONG>
<BR>
Nuclear Fuel Cycle and Materials Section, 
Division of Nuclear Power and Fuel Cycle
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B> 15 January 1997
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B> 15 May 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B> as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B> Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B> Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.B.13
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B></center>
<P>
Under the supervision of the Director of the Division of Nuclear
Power and the Fuel Cycle, to formulate and implement the Agency's
programme related to nuclear fuel cycle and materials.

<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
- To serve as the Head of the Nuclear Fuel Cycle and Materials Section
(NFC+M), which is responsible for the formulation and implementation
of the Agency's programme on nuclear fuel cycle and materials.  This
programme covers raw materials for reactor fuels, reactor fuel
technology and performance, spent fuel management, and other nuclear
fuel cycle technology issues and databases;
<BR>
- To propose and participate in establishing the medium term plan, to
plan and implement the Agency's programme and budget with respect to
the nuclear fuel cycle and materials;
<BR>
- To supervise the operation of the NFC&M Section, guiding, assisting
and supervising the Section's staff members in their work;
<BR>
- To participate and organize symposia, technical committees, advisory groups
and other scientific and technical meetings, to act as scientific secretary
for specific meetings, to prepare pertinent reports and documents;
<BR>
- To co-ordinate and support the Agency's technical co-operation
activities with developing Member States in relevant areas;
<BR>
- To represent the Agency at meetings on topics relevant to the
Section's activities sponsored by national and international
organizations;
<BR>
- To be responsible for liaison within the Agency and with national and
international organizations in the relevant area.

<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	Ph.D. or equivalent in nuclear engineering/physics,
chemistry and metallurgy.  At least 15 years of experience in the
area of nuclear fuel cycle and materials.  Knowledge of the
principles of human resource and financial management and ability to
apply this knowledge in managing assigned resources.  Ability to use
computer applications.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Ability to formulate future activities or projects in
the area of assignment.  Extensive experience in and detailed
knowledge of two or three technical areas of the nuclear fuel cycle
and materials.  Working or management experience at international
level. Good report writing capability.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.Ability to communicate fluently in written and spoken
English essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Renumeration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
<P>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=10 CELLSPACING=10 CELLPADDING=10>
<TR>
<TD><STRONG>Rate</TD>
<TD>Net Base Salary</TD>
<TD>Post Adjustment</STRONG></TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD><STRONG>Single</STRONG></TD>
<TD>$ 53,611.-</TD>
<TD>$-34,579.-</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD><STRONG>Dependency</STRONG></TD>
<TD>$ 57,806.-</TD>
<TD>$ 37,285.-</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>
<P>
Post Adjustment is variable and subject to change without notice.

<HR NOSHADE>
