<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.: 97/002</TITLE>
<META name="docid" content="97/002">
<META name="author" content="adpi">
<META name="expires" content="1997-05-15>
<META name="type" content="edit">
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR=#545454>
<B><I>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Collection Development Librarian</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.: 97/002</FONT>
<BR>
<STRONG>Grade:</STRONG>	P-2
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>
Organizational Unit</STRONG>
<BR>
VIC Library, Division of Scientific and Technical Information
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B> 15 January 1997
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B> 15 May 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B> as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B> Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B> Three years
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.C.03.a
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B></center>
<P>
Under the supervision of the Head, Technical Services to co-ordinate
the selection of materials appropriate for the Library at the Vienna
International Centre (VIC); to review and select all types of
material;  to
participate in the evaluation and monitoring of the strength and
depth of subject coverage in the Library's collections;  to consult
frequently with the members of the Library Consultative Committee on
the evaluation of recommendations for new material.

<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
- To review and recommend the selection of material for the VIC
Library;  to co-ordinate selection with the Library Consultative
Committees comprised of expert staff from the IAEA, United Nations Industrial Development
Organization (UNIDO) and the United Nations Office at Vienna (UNOV);
<BR> 
- To review journals and other sources of new publications, such as
subject bibliographies, publisher information, on-line resources for
new publications;  to analyse collections and determine subject areas
for special acquisitions; to develop lists of forthcoming books for
subject specialist teams to consider for selection;
<BR>
- To review unsolicited gift material and co-ordinate the acceptance of
material through the Acquisitions Staff for the purposes of gathering
statistics for gifts-in-kind;
<BR>
- To provide general reference services;
<BR>
- To participate in the establishment and revision of the subject areas to be
acquired for the Library through regular review of subject criteria
used for selection areas, consulting with vendors and library staff
as appropriate;
<BR>
- To administer the collection evaluation and assessment process and to
use on-line resources and standard subject bibliographies to analyse
the strength of Library collections by subject, use, age and other
criteria;
<BR>
- To provide training to Library support staff, and to prepare reports
and documentation regarding selection activities;
<BR>
- To carry out other duties as instructed, consistent with the level
of the post.
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	University degree in library/information science or
equivalent. Minimum of two years experience in a library.  The
incumbent must have excellent communication and negotiation skills in
order to work effectively
with the Library Consultative Committee comprised of expert staff
from the IAEA, UNIDO and UNOV organisations housed at the VIC. 
Ability to work co-operatively with a team comprising staff of
different nationalities.

<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Two years' experience in collection development.

<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.Excellent written and spoken English essential.

<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
<P>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=10 CELLSPACING=10 CELLPADDING=10>
<TR>
