<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Head, LAN Systems Support Unit</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.:  96/089</FONT>
<BR>
<STRONG>Grade:</STRONG>	P-4
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>
Organizational Unit
</STRONG>
<BR>
Computer Services Centre - Division of Scientific and Technical Information - Deparment of Nuclear Energy<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	14 November 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	13 March 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.A.05.e
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B>
<I>
In general</I>
</B>
</center>
<P>
Under the Head, Computer Services Centre, to manage the staff and
responsibilities of the LAN Systems Support Unit which provides
central LAN Server and computer communications services.
<P>
<CENTER>
<B>
<I>
In particular</I>
</B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To direct the technical planning, design, implementation and
maintenance of the hardware and software configuration for the
Agency's PC/LAN systems complex (LAN and PC operating systems, Server
hardware and software, and LAN systems administration).  To evaluate
LAN systems performance and optimization, hardware and software
requirements.  To implement new generations of operating systems,
develop and maintain operating procedures according to agreed service
levels and resolve complex technical problems in connection with the
utilization of this technology;
<DD>- To manage and technically support the hardware and software
configuration for providing Agency-wide computer communications
services (Email, Fax, etc.);
<DD>- To make provision for interfacing the Agency's in-house
communications system with other world-wide communication services. 
<DD>- To monitor and analyse system performance in order to ensure a high
level of availability;
<DD>- To manage the LAN Systems Support Unit and co-ordinate technical
interaction between Network Systems, Facility Management and
technical staff in other areas;
<DD>- To provide technical consultation to computer management on LAN
hardware and software standards' formulation.  To report on all
relevant service levels, including capacity, performance and
availability to users and management;
<DD>- To provide technical consultation for programmers and end-users to
assist them in identifying the causes of difficulties and to obtain
from them information relating to operating system, program product,
or hardware failures.
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>
QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B> University degree in computer science related field,
or equivalent, plus at least ten years' relevant practical experience,
of which at least two years should be in technical project management
and supervision of technical staff.  Experience in the effective
application of computer technology in a large international data
communications environment.  Detailed knowledge of LAN/PC operating
systems (specifically Windows NT Server), LAN-based communications
systems, LAN/mainframe connectivity, LAN Server architecture,
software tools, and systems management techniques.  An understanding
of networking operations, protocols (TCP/IP), and system
interconnection.  Good interpersonal skills with demonstrated ability
to manage a group of professional and technical support staff in a
multicultural environment.
<BR><B>Desirable:</B>	General knowledge of modern hardware and software
concepts, teleprocessing, and program products.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.  Knowledge of German an advantage.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P>
