<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/095</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR=#545454>
<B><I>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>	Section Head</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/095	</FONT>
<BR>
<STRONG>Grade:</STRONG>	P-5
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>Organizational Unit</STRONG>
<BR>
Safety Co-ordination Section - Department of Nuclear Safety
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	5 December 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	5 March 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.B.13
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the guidance of the Deputy Director General, Head of the
Department of Nuclear Safety, to lead co-ordination of the IAEA
functions on safety, including the development and establishment of
safety principles and standards.

<P>
<CENTER>
<B>
<I>
In particular</I>
</B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To serve as Head of the Safety Co-ordination Section which is
responsible for co-ordinating the following functional activities
carried out within the Department of Nuclear Safety:
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- development and establishment of fundamentals, standards and guides;
<P>
<DD>- evaluation of research activities, including co-ordinated research programmes;
<P>
<DD>- development and maintenance of departmental information services;
<P>
<DD>- performance of training courses;
<P>
<DD>- support of all Department-related technical co-operation activities;
<P>
<DD>- organization of conferences, symposia, seminars, consultants' groups
and other activities that promote research and exchange of
information in radiation, waste and nuclear safety;
<P>
<DD>- initiation of new activities.
</DL>
<P>
<DD>- To assist the Department Head in, for example, the collection of
relevant information and preparation of special studies and reports.
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B> Ph.D., or equivalent, in nuclear or other engineering
science.  Fifteen years' experience in a recognized organization dealing
with nuclear safety activities , some of which should be at the
managerial level.  Ability to apply the principles of finance and
human resources management in leading a diverse work force in a
multi-cultural environment.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French Russian or Spanish
essential.  Ability to communicate fluently in written and spoken
English essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P>
