<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.: 96/097</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR=#545454>
<B><I>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Animal Scientist</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.: 96/097</FONT>
<BR>
<STRONG>Grade:</STRONG> P-3
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>Organizational Unit</STRONG>
<BR>
Animal Production and Health Section - Joint FAO/IAEA Division of Nuclear Techniques in Food and Agriculture - Department of Research and Isotopes
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B> 18 December 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B> 18 April 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B> 1 November 1997	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B> Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B> Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B> Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B> 1.H.01.b
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the direct supervision of the Head, Animal Production and
Health Section, to technically assist in the implementation of the
sub-programme of the Animal Production and Health Section by
supporting scientists in developing countries who are undertaking
studies using nuclear techniques to improve animal production.  To
provide technical support for FAO/IAEA research contracts and
Technical Co-operation (TC) projects in this field.
<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To co-ordinate FAO-IAEA Co-ordinated Research Programmes (CRPs) in
the field of animal nutrition/reproduction.  Current programmes deal
with feed supplementation strategies, improvement of artificial
insemination services, the analysis of purine derivatives and the
development of assays for  tannin determination in leguminous plants;
<P>
<DD>- To provide technical support for TC projects in the field of animal
nutrition and reproduction;
<P>
<DD>- To organise training courses, including preparation of the
prospectus, timetable and evaluation of applicants;
<P>
<DD>- To maintain a world-wide programme of support for the use of
standardized and validated radioimmunoassay (RIA) kits for
measurement of progesterone in support of CRPs and IAEA TC projects. 
This includes the operation of an external quality assurance programme to assess proficiency in the use
of RIA kits;
<P>
<DD>- To assist in the development and supervision of the technical aspects
of the animal production and health sub-programme.
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B> University degree (DVM, PhD. or equivalent) in animal
production or veterinary medicine. Six years of practical experience in animal
nutrition/reproduction.  Working knowledge of immunoassay with
particular reference to RIA and/or enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay
(ELISA).  Working experience in developing countries.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B> Experience in the development of systems for
improving animal productivity through nutritional interventions, the
use of isotope-based molecular methodologies for assessing and
improving animal productivity; computerized databases and
spreadsheets; the use of statistics for data evaluation;  the
management of international projects.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B> Fluency in English, French, Russian of Spanish
essential. Ability to communicate fluently in written and spoken
English essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars  and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P>
<CENTER>
