<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/073	
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<center>
<font color=#545454>
<b><i>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</font>
</center>
<HR NOSHADE>
<center>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Section Head
</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/073	
</FONT>
<BR>
<strong>Grade:</strong>	P-5
<HR NOSHADE>
<strong>Organizational Unit</strong>
<br>
Soil and Water Management & Crop Nutrition Section - 	Joint FAO/IAEA Division of Nuclear Techniques in Food and Agriculture - Department of Research and Isotopes
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	3 September 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	3 January 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.H.07.b
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the supervision of the Director, to provide technical and
managerial leadership in formulating, guiding and monitoring the
performance of the Joint FAO/IAEA programme to assist Member States
in applying isotope and radiation methods in soil science and plant
nutrition.

<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To supervise staff of the Soil and Water Management & Crop Nutrition
Section and to provide technical guidance to the laboratory support
programme conducted by the Soil Science Unit of the FAO/IAEA
Agriculture and Biotechnology Laboratory;
<DD>- To develop sound co-ordinated research programmes, evaluate research
contract proposals, review requests for renewals, organize research
co-ordination meetings, collate information and edit publications as
necessary;
<DD>- To evaluate requests for technical co-operation projects, advise on
the type of equipment needed, assist in finding qualified experts for
technical co-operation projects by evaluating their technical
competence and evaluate experts' field reports;  to evaluate
fellowship applicants technically, advise on their placement and
guide their programme of study;  to plan training courses and help
secure instructors;
<DD>- To prepare the scientific programme of relevant scientific meetings,
to serve as scientific secretary for such meetings and to
prepare/edit the resulting reports or proceedings for publication;
<DD>- To provide relevant scientific information to other divisions of the
IAEA and FAO;
<DD>- To represent the Organizations on scientific missions and interact
with other organizations and potential donors for programmes;
<DD>- To assemble and review information on current developments in the
scientific area of relevance to the Section's activities.
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<center>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</center>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	Ph.D. or equivalent in soil science or agronomy. 
Fifteen years of research and project management experience in using
isotopes and radiation methods for developing integrated nutrient and
water management strategies for cropping systems.  Knowledge of the
principles of human resources and financial management and ability to
apply this knowledge for managing assigned resources.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Relevant experience in developing countries and with
international programmes.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish essential.
<P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
<P>
<CENTER>
