<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/096</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR=#545454>
<B><I>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Technical Standards Specialist</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/096</FONT>
<BR>
<STRONG>Grade:</STRONG>	P-4
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>Organizational Unit</STRONG>
<BR>
Section for Standardization - Division of Concepts and Planning - Department of Safeguards
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	5 December 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	4 April 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.J.07
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the supervision of the Section Head, to participate in
standardization activities related to safeguards implementation, with
particular emphasis on new measures associated with the strengthening
of safeguards;  specifically to develop or assist in the development
of guidelines, procedures, instructions and related performance
standards.  To provide information and advice on standardization
matters to staff in the Department.

<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To prepare standardized procedures for safeguards implementation with
a particular view to new measures aimed at the strengthening of
safeguards;
<DD>- To provide assistance to the Divisions  Operations, Department of
Safeguards, in the areas of computerized inspection reports and
standards;  to maintain relevant requirements, procedures and
instructions;
<DD>- To analyze, prepare or revise standardized definitions, policies and
procedures on aspects of safeguards development, support and
operations;
<DD>- To contribute to the preparation, review and negotiation of
Subsidiary Arrangements and related IAEA policy, as well as model
provisions;
<DD>- To participate in safeguards inspections, as appropriate.
</DL>
<P>
<I>NOTE:</I>	The incumbent of the post is occupationally exposed, in the
performance of his/her work, to radiation or radioactive substances
and will be submitted to an appropriate monitoring programme,
according to the Agency's Radiation Protection Rules and Procedures.
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B> University degree with emphasis on a nuclear
discipline, supplemented by practical experience in areas relevant to
safeguards or nuclear material management and control;  demonstrated
experience in the design and implementation of safeguards measures at
nuclear fuel cycle facilities.  At least ten years' experience of
which five years should be at the international level.  Good drafting
skills in English are essential.  Detailed knowledge of IAEA
inspection practices is required.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars  and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=10 CELLSPACING=10 CELLPADDING=10>
