<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.: 96/088</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR=#545454>
<B><I>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Section Head</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2> Vacancy Notice No.: 96/088</FONT>
<BR>
<STRONG>Grade:</STRONG>	P-5
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>
Organizational Unit</STRONG>
<BR>
Section OA3 - Division of Operations A -  Department of Safeguards
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	14 November 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	13 March 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.J.07
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B></center>
<P>
Under the supervision of the Division Director, the Section Head is
responsibile for directing and performing safeguards activities in
accordance with relevant safeguards agreements, both within the
Section and in co-ordination with the other Sections in the Division.
<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To direct the work of the staff of the Section, with
particular emphasis on the functions indicated below:
<DD>- To organize and direct the Section by monitoring and controlling the
activities of its staff.  To supervise the carrying out of inspection
programmes and ensure appropriate input for procedures,
instrumentation as well as technical and computer equipment relating
to the Section.  To maintain technical correspondence with respect to
routine implementation of safeguards;
<DD>- To provide appropriate input for scheduling and preparation of
inspection activities.  To ensure adherence to travel policies and
procedures.  To perform inspections, to oversee the performance of
inspections and evaluate inspector field performance, including pre-
and post-inspection activities.  To maintain appropriate reporting
procedures and practices;
<DD>- To conduct Section meetings and participate in other Divisional and
Departmental co-ordination meetings;
<DD>- To evaluate accounting reports and notifications in connection with
safeguards implementation.  To review and evaluate inspection reports
and statements;
<DD>- To provide input to safeguards agreements, subsidiary arrangements
and facility attachments and participate as necessary in negotiations
of relevance to the Section.
</DL>
<I>NOTE:</I>	The incumbent of the post may be exposed, in the performance
of his/her work, to radiation or radioactive substances and will be
submitted to an appropriate programme in accordance with the Agency's
Radiation Protection Rules and Procedures.
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>
QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B> Advanced university degree in chemistry, physics,
engineering or equivalent.  At least 15 years of experience in the
nuclear industry, nuclear research or nuclear related international
or government service of which at least five years should be in 
safeguards.  Good knowledge of the principles and practices of human
resource management.  Demonstrated experience in progressively
responsible positions of a supervisory/managerial nature.  Ability to
guide effectively a team of professional and support staff within a
multicultural and dynamic environment.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Experience in the efficient use of information
treated by electronic data processing.
<BR><B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.  Excellent command of oral and written English.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=10 CELLSPACING=10 CELLPADDING=10>
<TR>
