<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.:  96/087</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<FONT COLOR=#545454>
<B><I>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</FONT>
</CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>NDA Equipment Specialist
</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.:  96/087</FONT>
<BR>
<STRONG>Grade:</STRONG>	P-4
<HR NOSHADE>
<STRONG>
Organizational Unit
</STRONG>
<BR>
Section for Equipment Management - Division of Development and Technical Support - Deparment of Safeguards
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	14 November 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	13 March 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.B.07.b
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the supervision of a Unit Head, to co-ordinate the Group for
Calibration and Maintenance, which is responsible for the setup,
calibration, testing, commissioning, maintenance and repair of all
safeguards non-destructive assay (NDA) and unattended radiation
monitoring equipment. 
<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To co-ordinate, supervise and provide technical expertise to the
Group, as well as to determine schedules and set goals and priorities
for the staff in the Group;
<DD>- To provide a technical overview and guidance for the work, and to
engineer solutions to problems encountered;
<DD>- To apply diagnostic and troubleshooting methods to failure analysis
and repair of NDA equipment;
<DD>- To develop and implement standardization and systemization of NDA
equipment and automated setup and calibration equipment;
<DD>- To work in co-operation with suppliers and manufacturers of NDA
equipment to adapt equipment to Agency-specific needs;
<DD>- To develop and prepare technical specifications, acceptance testing
procedures and other documentation;
<DD>- To assist the Unit Head in the administration and management of the Unit;
<DD>- To undertake other technical duties as required.
</DL>
<I>NOTE:</I>	The incumbent of the post may be exposed, in the performance
of his/her work, to radiation or radioactive substances and will be
submitted to an appropriate programme, in accordance with the
Agency's Radiation Protection Rules and Procedures.
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>
QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</CENTER>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	University degree in engineering, or nuclear physics,
with specialization in electronics and analysis technology;
demonstrated capability in co-ordination of tasks and supervision of
staff;  technical competence in the field of nuclear monitoring
electronics and safeguards instrumentation;  technical competence in
the field of NDA equipment engineering and application;  technical
competence in the field of equipment installation in nuclear
facilities;  technical competence in the troubleshooting and
maintenance of electronic instrumentation;  ten years' relevant
professional experience, some of which were in an international
environment;  demonstrated skills in communication and in the
preparation of technical and management reports.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	International safeguards inspection experience. 
Electrical and mechanical equipment manufacturing experience.
<BR><B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish is
essential.  Fluency in technical English is essential, German would
be an asset.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=10 CELLSPACING=10 CELLPADDING=10>
<TR>
