<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- Study and understand existing procedures for PC-applicability;
<DD>- Make recommendations on PC-based solutions to problems considering
the cost, capability, and functional requirements;
<DD>- Perform functional and data analysis;
<DD>- Design, program, test and document highly complex computer programs;
<DD>- Survey software and hardware products for possible utilization and
make recommendations related to safeguards evaluation.
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<center>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</center>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	University degree preferably in computer science or a
related field;  experience in the design and development of PC-based
systems in a Windows environment;  experience with Windows-based
application development tools;  six years relevant professional
experience.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Experience with:  Microsoft SQL Server, ADABAS,
NATURAL, International Safeguards;  knowledge of and experience in
system development methodologies;  experience with Visual Basic or Access.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.  Ability to communicate fluently in writing and spoken
English is essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
