<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<center>
<font color=#545454>
<b><i>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</font>
</center>
<HR NOSHADE>
<center>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Systems Analyst (2 Posts)
</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.: 96/084	
</FONT>
<BR>
<strong>Grade:</strong>	P-4
<HR NOSHADE>
<strong>Organizational Unit 
</strong>
<br>
Section for Data Processing Development (IDD) - Division of Safeguards Information Treatment (SGIT) - Department of Safeguards
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	17 October 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	17 February 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.A.05.b
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the supervision of a Unit Head, to specify, design, develop and
implement computerized safeguards systems and develop and manage
projects which are integral to the PC-based Inspection Field Support
System (IFSS) and which require interface with other PC-based
systems.  These applications are either LAN-based or for in-field
use.  To plan and schedule projects and supervise and guide staff
assigned to these projects.  To participate in developing,
maintaining and applying software quality assurance procedures.

<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To review the proposals and solutions made by development programmers
and systems analysts, especially regarding cost-effectiveness,
technical soundness and user acceptance;
<DD>- As project manager and systems analyst to:
<UL>
<LI>study and understand the existing data treatment procedures;
<LI>draw conclusions as to the cost-effectiveness of computer solutions;
<LI>perform functional and data analysis;
<LI>develop analysis, design and detailed design specifications;
<LI>participation in and/or management of the implementation including
testing, user documentation, field testing.
</UL>
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<center>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</center>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	University degree preferably in computer science or
related field;  experience in the design and development of PC-based
systems in a Windows environment;  experience with Windows-based
application development tools;  knowledge of and experience in system
development methodologies;  project management experience; 
experience in staff management;  ten  years relevant professional
experience.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Experience with:  Microsoft SQL Server, ADABAS,
NATURAL, International Safeguards;  Experience with Visual Basic or
Access.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.  Ability to communicate fluently in writing and spoken
English is essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
