<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/083	</TITLE>
<META name="docid" content="96/083">
<META name="author" content="adpi (public information)">
<META name="expires" content="1997-02-17">
<META name="type" content="edit">
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<center>
<font color=#545454>
<b><i>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</font>
</center>
<HR NOSHADE>
<center>
<FONT SIZE=+2>	Systems Analyst
</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/083	
</FONT>
<BR>
<strong>Grade:</strong>	P-4
<HR NOSHADE>
<strong>Organizational Unit
</strong>
<br>
Section for Data Processing Development (IDD) - Division of Safeguards Information Treatment (SGIT) - Department of Safeguards
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	17 October 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	17 February 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.A.05.b
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the supervision of a Unit Head, to specify, design, develop and
implement computerized safeguards systems and to develop and manage
projects which are an integral part of the information analysis
function for safeguards-related data (both open-source and in-house).
 These systems are either UNIX-based (typically running on a Sun
workstation) or involve PC clients retrieving data from a UNIX
server.  To install, maintain and adapt third-party software packages
used for information analysis.  To plan and schedule projects and
supervise and guide staff assigned to these projects.
<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>
In particular</I>
</B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To review the proposals and solutions made by development programmers
and systems analysts, especially regarding cost-effectiveness,
technical soundness and user acceptance;
<DD>- As project manager and systems analyst to:
<UL>
<LI>study and understand the existing data treatment procedures;
<LI>draw conclusions as to the cost-effectiveness of computer solutions;
<LI>perform functional and data analysis;
<LI>develop analysis, design and detailed design specifications;
participation in and/or management of the implementation including
testing, user documentation, field testing and training.
</UL>
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<center><B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</center>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	University degree preferably in computer science or
related field.  Experience with the UNIX operating system, UNIX
utility programs and UNIX shell scripts; experience in the design and
development of UNIX-based systems running under the X-Windows
environment;  knowledge of and experience in system development
methodologies;  project management experience and experience in staff
management;  ten  years relevant professional experience.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Experience with:  SQL databases such as Oracle or SQL
Server, International Safeguards;  experience with Visual Basic or
Access.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.  Ability to communicate fluently in written and spoken
English is essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P>
