<HEAD>
<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.: 96/082</TITLE>
<META name="docid" content="96/082">
<META name="author" content="adpi (public information)">
<META name="expires" content="199-02-17">
<META name="type" content="edit">
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<center>
<font color=#545454>
<b><i>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</font>
</center>
<HR NOSHADE>
<center>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Senior Training Officer (Instrumentation)
</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.: 96/082
</FONT>
<BR>
<strong>Grade:</strong>	P-4
<HR NOSHADE>
<strong>Organizational Unit</strong>
<br>
Section for Safeguards Training - Division of Development and Technical Support - Department of Safeguards
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	17 October 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	17 February 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.A.06.g
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the supervision of the Section Head, to assist in the training
of inspectors in non-destructive assay (NDA), containment and
surveillance (C/S) and equipment and procedures.
<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To prepare and update training materials for the relevant parts of
the Introductory Course on Agency Safeguards (ICAS) and other
advanced/refresher courses related to NDA and C/S, and to deliver
selected lectures;
<DD>- To prepare instructional training aids including videotapes and
course procedures on selected NDA & C/S topics;
<DD>- To provide instruction on NDA and C/S for new and experienced
inspectors in formal and individual situations;
<DD>- To serve as a resource person for the review of draft NDA procedures
for usability during training exercises;
<DD>- To schedule the availability and use of NDA and C/S training
equipment for internal and external courses and co-ordinate with the
Section for Equipment Management (DEM) to assure proper maintenance
and readiness of training equipment;  
<DD>- To advise on equipment needs as
new technologies are adopted as Agency standard; 
<DD>- To provide the
Section for Training (DTR) management with periodic schedules and
projections of training equipment needs;
<DD>- To develop calibrations for training purposes on NDA training
equipment using nuclear materials for the purpose of demonstration
and inspector training;
<DD>- To organize, direct, manage and supervise training teams assigned to
provide NDA and C/S courses and sessions;
<DD>- To develop evaluation criteria to determine training effectiveness at
course level and ultimately the training impact on the ability of the
inspectorate to perform NDA verifications of nuclear material;
<DD>- To assist in other inspector training activities, as requested.
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<center>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</center>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	Advanced university degree or equivalent in science,
engineering or allied disciplines.  Extensive experience in providing
technical training.  At least 10 years experience in the nuclear
industry with demonstrated ability to manage human resources in the
training arena.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Knowledge of IAEA Safeguards inspection activities,
organization and implementation of international training activities.
 Knowledge of IAEA NDA and C/S equipment and procedures.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.  Ability to communicate fluently in written and spoken
English is essential.
<HR NOSHADE><P>Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
<P>
<CENTER>
