<font color=#545454>
<b><i>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</font>
</center>
<HR NOSHADE>
<center>
<FONT SIZE=+2>	Senior Training Officer (Training Specialist)
</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.:	96/081	
</FONT>
<BR>
<strong>Grade:</strong>	P-4
<HR NOSHADE>
<strong>Organizational Unit</strong><br>	
Section for Safeguards Training - Division of Development and Technical Support - Department of Safeguards
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	17 October 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	17 February 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.A.06.g
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the supervision of the Section Head, the incumbent will be
responsible for the implementation of a systematic approach to
training with the aim of establishing and maintaining the
qualifications and competence of international safeguards inspectors,
of the support programme staff within the Department of Safeguards,
and of Member States' personnel.
<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To monitor on a continuous basis, the training programme in order to
identify the training needs of personnel in the Department of
Safeguards and  the competencies required to perform safeguards
inspections and support activities, recommending policy revisions as
necessary;
<DD>- To convert the competencies identified above into training objectives
and to sequence those training objectives into training plans for
basic, advanced and refresher training courses and workshops;
<DD>- To supervise the development of course materials for the
implementation of training programmes;
<DD>- To facilitate the implementation of the training programme by
conducting the training using materials and lesson plans developed as
specified;
<DD>- To liaise with other sections and divisions in the Department and
within the Secretariat concerning training programmes and the
recruitment of lecturers and course participants;
<DD>- To evaluate training courses and workshops by determining the
effectiveness, efficiency and impact of training programmes and to
identify whether and where revisions or improvements are needed;
<DD>- To provide instruction in selected topics of the Safeguards training
programmes;
<DD>- To ascertain the appropriate Member State support for specified
training programmes and solicit assistance in the development, design
and implementation of the programme;
<DD>- To serve as Task Officer for the specified training programme,
co-ordinating the efforts of the Member State Support Programme;
<DD>- To design, implement and establish criteria for the evaluation of
training courses;
<DD>- To assist in other training activities, as requested.
</DL>
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<center>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</center>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	Advanced university degree or equivalent in sciences,
engineering or allied disciplines.  At least ten years of varied
experience in the nuclear industry, of which a minimum of four years,
with responsibility for directing and/or conducting training courses
and programmes using systematic instructional training methodologies.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Knowledge of presentation skills and presentation
graphics programs. Knowledge of/or experience in matters concerning
non-proliferation issues or IAEA safeguards activities.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish
essential.  Ability to communicate fluently in written and spoken
English is essential.
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
<P>
