<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE> Senior Safeguards Analyst</TITLE></HEAD><BODY bgcolor=#ffffff><center><font color=#545454><b>
<i>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B></font>
</center><HR NOSHADE><center><FONT SIZE=+2>	Senior Safeguards Analyst<BR> Vacancy Notice No.: 96/077</FONT><BR><strong>Grade:</strong>	P-5
<HR NOSHADE><strong>Organizational Unit</strong><br>	System Studies Section
	Division of Concepts and Planning
<BR></CENTER><P><UL><LI><B>Date:</B>10 October 1996<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	10 February 1997    
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.J.07
</UL><P><HR width=40% NOSHADE><CENTER><B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B><HR width=40% NOSHADE><B><I>In general</I></B></center><P>
Under the supervision of the Head of the System Studies Section, to supervise and participate in various studies related to advanced safeguards concepts, or to safeguards concepts and technologies in areas where existing approaches require modification;  to organize, prepare working papers for and conduct Consultants and Advisory Group Meetings;  to participate in related activities as assigned.

<P><CENTER><B><I>In particular</I></B></CENTER><P>- To analyse and evaluate the effectiveness of advanced safeguards concepts, as well as to develop advanced safeguards approaches and procedures in order to make safeguards more effective and efficient;<BR>
- To develop safeguards approaches and procedures for various fuel cycle facilities incorporating advanced safeguards concepts;<BR>
- To serve as Task Officer for Member State Support Programme tasks in the above areas;<BR>
- To prepare working documents for consideration within the Department of Safeguards and by international advisory and consultants groups;<BR>
- Subject to the approval of the Board of Governors, to function as a safeguards inspector, i.e. to prepare and carry out Agency safeguards inspections and prepare reports thereon;<BR>
- To carry out such other functions as may be entrusted to him or her.<BR>

<P><HR width=25% NOSHADE>


<B>NOTE:</B>	The incumbent of the post may be exposed, in the performance of his/her work, to radiation or radioactive substances and will be submitted to an appropriate monitoring programme, according to the Agency's Radiation Protection Rules and Procedures.


<P><HR width=25% NOSHADE><center><B>QUALIFICATIONS</B><HR width=25% NOSHADE></center><P><B>Essential:</B>	Ph.D., or equivalent, university degree in nuclear technology, chemical or nuclear engineering or related disciplines.  At least 15 years nuclear experience, preferably including extensive experience in the application of systems analysis/operations research methods to safeguards problems.  Intimate knowledge of peaceful nuclear process operations.  Experience in the management of human and financial resources.  Ability to organize and lead multicultural teams.

<BR><B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish essential.  Ability to write technical reports in English essential.



<HR NOSHADE><P>Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars 
                          and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.<P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=10 CELLSPACING=10 CELLPADDING=10><TR><TD><STRONG>Rate</TD><TD>Net Base Salary</TD><TD>Post Adjustment</STRONG></TD></TR><TR><TD><STRONG>Single</STRONG></TD><TD>$53,611.-		</TD><TD>$37,742.-
