<TITLE>Vacancy Notice No.: 96/072</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#ffffff>
<center>
<font color=#545454>
<b><i>Applications are invited from suitably qualified women as well as men</I></B>
</font>
</center>
<HR NOSHADE>
<center>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Safeguards Data Evaluator</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2>Vacancy Notice No.: 96/072</FONT>
<BR>
<strong>Grade:</strong>	P-3
<HR NOSHADE>
<strong>Organizational Unit</strong>
<br>
Section for Statistical Analysis - Division of Concepts and Planning - Department of Safeguards
<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><B>Date:</B>	3 September 1996
<LI><B>Closing Date:</B>	3 January 1997
<LI><B>Reporting Date:</B>	as soon as possible	
<LI><B>Duty Station:</B>	Vienna
<LI><B>Type of Appointment:</B>	Fixed-term
<LI><B>Duration of Appointment:</B>	Three years
<LI><B>CCOG Code:</B>	1.M.02.b/1.J.07
</UL>
<P>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<CENTER>
<B>DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</B>
<HR width=40% NOSHADE>
<B><I>In general</I></B>
</center>
<P>
Under the supervision of the Head of the Section for Statistical
Analysis, to co-ordinate the processing of destructive analysis (DA)
non-destructive analysis (NDA) and environmental sample measurement
results.  To contribute to the setting up and implementation of a
routine evaluation system for environmental samples.  To design and
implement advanced statistical procedures for the evaluation of
environmental and other safeguards data.

<P>
<CENTER>
<B><I>In particular</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<DL>
<DD>- To co-ordinate and participate in the processing and evaluation of
destructive analysis (DA),  non-destructive analysis, and
environmental sample measurement results and to prepare routine and
special evaluation reports on the quality of measurements as a
service to inspectors;  this requires the application of statistical
evaluation methods, extensive use of computers and knowledge of
nuclear processes and related analytical techniques;
<DD>- To contribute to the design and implementation of a routine
evaluation system for environmental samples;  this requires database
design and development of evaluation software;
<DD>- To contribute to the design, testing and implementation of advanced
statistical and data presentation procedures;  this requires handling
of large databases and implementation of modern software tools;
<DD>- Subject to approval of the Board of Governors, to function as a
Safeguards Inspector;  i.e., to prepare for, carry out and
subsequently report on Agency Safeguards Inspections.
</DL>
<P>
<I>NOTE:</I>	The incumbent of the post may be exposed, in the performance
of his/her work, to radiation or radioactive substances and will be
submitted to an appropriate monitoring programme, according to the
Agency's Radiation Protection Rules and Procedures.
<P>
Filling of this post is contingent upon General Conference
approval of the 1997 budget.
<P>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
<center>
<B>QUALIFICATIONS</B>
<HR width=25% NOSHADE>
</center>
<P>
<B>Essential:</B>	Advanced university degree in statistics, nuclear
engineering or analytical chemistry.  Six years of experience in
nuclear material measurements and related computerized data
evaluation.
<BR>
<B>Desirable:</B>	Experience of database management, including
programming in higher programming languages.  Knowledge of the
nuclear fuel cycle.
<BR>
<B>Languages:</B>	Fluency in English, French, Russian or Spanish essential.
<P>
<HR NOSHADE>
<P>
Remuneration is quoted in annual amounts in US dollars and is deemed to be exempt from National Income Tax.
