<HEAD>
<TITLE>PR/11 - 18 May 1995 - New Director of International Centre for Theoretical Physics, Trieste </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
18 May 1995 (PR 95/11)
<CENTER>
<H3>New Director of International Centre for Theoretical Physics, Trieste</H3>
 </CENTER>        
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
<P>
         The Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) Dr. Hans Blix,
         in consultation with the Director General of UNESCO, Prof. Federico Mayor, has
         appointed Prof. Miguel A. Virasoro from Argentina as the new Director of the
         International Centre for Theoretical Physics based in Trieste, Italy.
<P>         
         Prof. Virasoro has had a wide and distinguished international scientific career,
         specializing in theoretical physics. Born in 1940, Prof. Virasoro received his degree and
         doctorate in Physics at the University of Buenos Aires. Following positions in countries
         including the United States, Argentina, France, and Italy, he worked at CERN in Geneva
         in the early '80s. Thereafter he returned to Italy, where he is currently a Professor in
         the Department of Physics at the University of Rome.
<P>         
         In 1994, Professor Virasoro was the first person to be awarded the prestigious
         Rammal Medal by the Socit Franaise de Physique and the cole Normale Suprieure
         Foundation for his outstanding services to science in the Mediterranean region.
<P>         
         He is expected to assume his new position as of June 1995. His predecessor, Prof.
         Abdul Salam of Pakistan, will continue to serve as President of the Centre.
<P>
