<head>
<title>PR/1 - 6 January 1995 - IAEA Programme of Scientific Meetings for 1995</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<hr size=1 noshade>
6 January 1995 (PR 95/1)
<h3>IAEA Programme of Scientific Meetings for 1995</h3>
<hr noshade size=1>
<p>
Six scientific conferences and symposia will be convened by the IAEA in 1995.
<P>
Conferences and Symposia:
<OL>
<LI>Symposium on Isotopes in Water Resources Management, Vienna, Austria, 20-24 March
<LI>Symposium on Environmental Impact of Radioactive Releases, Vienna, Austria, 8-12 May
<LI>Symposium on the Use of Induced Mutations and Molecular Techniques for Crop Improvement, Vienna, Austria, 19-23 June
<LI>Symposium on Tomography in Nuclear Medicine: Present Status and Future Prospects, Vienna, Austria, 21-25 August
<LI>International Conference on Advances in the Operational Safety of Nuclear Power Plants, Vienna, Austria, 4-8 September
<LI>International Symposium on Electricity, Health and the Environment: Comparative Assessment in Support of Decision Making, Stockholm, Sweden, 17-20 October
</OL>
<P>
In addition there will be five scientific seminars:
<OL>
<LI>Seminar on Management of Ageing of Research Reactors, Geesthact, near Hamburg, Germany, 8-12 May
<LI>Seminar on the Advancement in the Implementation of the New Basic Safety Standards (Experience in Applying the 1990 Recommendations of ICRP), Vienna, Austria, 14-18 August
<LI>Seminar on the Requirements for the Safe Management of Radioactive Waste, Vienna, Austria, 28 August - 1 September
<LI>Second FAO/IAEA Seminar for Africa on Animal Trypanosomiasis: Vector and Disease Control Using Nuclear Techniques, Zanzibar, Tanzania, 4-8 September
<LI>Regional Seminar for Asia and the Pacific on Radiotherapy Dosimetry: Radiation Dose in Radiotherapy from Prescription to Delivery, Bangkok, Thailand, 27-28 November
</OL>
<P>
 Detailed information may be obtained from the appropriate national authorities in
Member States, such as the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the National Atomic Energy
Commission, or by writing directly to the IAEA, P.O. Box 100, Vienna International
Centre, A-1400 Vienna, Austria.
<P>
Participants are designated either by the Government of a Member State of the
IAEA or the co-sponsoring organization, or by an international organization invited to
participate. If individuals wish to attend, they are admitted only as observers. All meetings
are open to the press.
<P>
The IAEA will publish the proceedings of the conferences and symposia as soon as
possible. Requests for publications should be sent directly to the Division of Publications,
IAEA, Vienna, or can  be obtained from the designated sales agents in Member States.
<P>
