<head>
<title>NF - World Survey of Activities in Controlled Fusion Research</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h2><img src="/worldatom/images/fusion.gif" align=middle> <font size=7>n u c l e a r&#160;</font><font size=4>&#160;&#160;</font><font size=7> f u s i o n&#160;</font></h2>
<h2><font size=4><strong>WORLD SURVEY OF ACTIVITIES IN CONTROLLED FUSION RESEARCH</strong></font></h2>
<hr>
<p><strong>WORLD SURVEY OF ACTIVITIES IN CONTROLLED FUSION RESEARCH, 1994 EDITION</strong><br>
Special Supplement to Nuclear Fusion, IAEA, Vienna 1994<br>
Editor: C. Bobeldijk (retired end of June 1996)<br>
STI/PUB/023/SPS/1994, &#160;ISBN 92-0-103594-2, ISSN 0029-5515, &#160;Price: 1280 Austrian Schillings.<br>
<br>
<strong>Foreword:</strong><br>
<br>
Up till 1991, six editions of the Nuclear Fusion Supplement 'World Survey of Activities in Controlled Fusion Research' were produced. The later editions 
contained, besides comprehensive information on institutes and personnel, tables with details of the experimental and theoretical activities in virtually all the world's 
institutes active in nuclear fusion research. These tables have now been replaced by short descriptions of the main activities complemented with references to the 
1991 tables where additional information can be found. <br>
<br>
The availability of separate files for each institute has led to a change of format of the World Survey from book to loose-leaf system. This has the advantage that 
information and last minute corrections can be induced and that updates of single institutes can be distributed and included during the time between the regular 
editions, even by the institutes themselves. The ultimate goal will be to make the World Survey available in electronic format. <br>
<br>
This edition of the World Survey consists mainly of two parts: 'Laboratories and Scientific Staff' ' and the 'Personnel Index'. The two parts are preceded by a short 
list of institutes ordered alphabetically according to country and city to simplify the search for these institutes, and followed by a list of table headings of the 1991 
tables referred to in the individual submissions. <br>
<br>
The responsible IAEA staff members were C. Bobeldijk, L. Dias-Noronha, M. Bergamini-R&ouml;edler and F. Hannak. </p>
<hr>
<p align=center>[<a href="index.html">NF Home Page</a>][<a href="contents.htm">NF Contents Page</a>][<a href="subscrip.htm">Subscriptions</a>][<a href="calendar.htm">Fusion Calendar</a>][<a href="boe.htm">Board of Editors</a>][<a href="nfoffice.htm">NF Office</a>][<a href="manuscri.htm">Manuscript Submission</a>][<a href="author.htm">Author Index</a>]</p>
